name: dewlit-logic
code:
import os
import json
import numpy as np
import onnxruntime as ort


import gdown
if not os.path.isfile('model.onnx'):
    gdown.download(
        # 'https://drive.google.com/uc?id=1Qx9JPSaLQmpg7UNSMqVrvnMqyCImlTPX',
        'https://drive.google.com/uc?id=1P-qbbDUtbwnGOnqx3TDIjPjQiRSbXax_',
        'model.onnx')

def init_context(context):
    context.user_data.model = model = ort.InferenceSession('model.onnx')
    context.user_data.input_name = model.get_inputs()[0].name

input_length = 256

def handler(context, event):
    model = context.user_data.model
    input_name = context.user_data.input_name

    x = event.body
    x = x.decode('utf-8') if isinstance(x, bytes) else x
    x = json.loads(x) if isinstance(x, str) else x
    context.logger.info_with(str(x))
    orig_length = len(x)

    # evaluate
    x = np.array(x, dtype=np.float32)
    x = np.pad(x, ((input_length - len(x), 0),))
    outputs = model.run(None, {input_name: x[None, :, None]})
    y = np.array(outputs)[0, 0, :, 1]
    # squash predictions for zero inputs
    y = y * (x > 0)
    y = np.nan_to_num(y, copy=False, nan=0.0)
    y = y[-orig_length if orig_length else len(y):]

    # return a response with the result
    return context.Response(
        body=json.dumps(y.tolist()),
        headers={},
        content_type='application/json',
        status_code=200)
